title: ComicPirates Weeklies Archive (CPWA) (2012-04 - 2014-10) (N=616)
description:
CONTAINS: 616 torrent metadata files, covering all Weeklies (plus a few Monthlies
and one Annual) posted in the stated period by  <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipJ" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipJ</a>
and  <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipjolly" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipjolly</a>   , in five lightly compressed archives.

FORMATTING: I drastically abbreviated and systematized the filenames, which now consist of four snippets (or "tokens", in programmerese), separated by underscores.

   Example (Weekly):  7696241_2012.09.26_HL.03.R1_T-X.torrent
   Example (Monthly): 7743121_2012.10.00_HL.02.R2_A-Z.torrent
   Example (Annual):  9450218_2013.00.00_0D.01.R1_9-Z.torrent

   First snippet:     TPB torrent identifier. I put this on the left to get them in
   chronological order; can be used to construct the upload page URL directly.

   Second snippet:    Date per torrent name. Ordinary dates mean Weeklies, while the
   ones with a 00 in the day/month position are Monthlies/Annuals, respectively.

   Third snippet:     Type of torrent. In order, 0D(ay) or H(it)L(ist), part number,
   and revision (1 for regulars, 2 for "fixes", "repacks", "fillers", et cetera).

   Fourth snippet:    Initial letters of first and last files contained. Note that
   this is meaningless in the rare cases in which torrents were not alphabetized.

NOTE: Any mistakes made in the original titles are (deliberately) preserved here, so trust the first and last tokens rather than the ones in-between, whenever in doubt
